    <note>Huang(2) Feigong [18996] There are several probable copying errors in the records for this lineage included in the Fujian TZ and Sanshan zhi jinshi lists. Sanshan zhi, 32.41b has Gang's [19005] great grandfather as Zhigong, grandfather as Wen(2) [18998] and father as Shen. Shen is also listed as the father of both Gang and Yu(9) [19006] in Fujian TZ and Sanshan zhi. Shite [19002] is listed as a son of a Shu in Fujian TZ, 149.25a and in Sanshan zhi. There are no entries for Zhigong, Shen or Shu in either source. I am assuming, therefore, that Zhigong (not in dataset) is a brother or cousin of Feigong, who moved to Luoyuan. Shen must be an error for Yue(3) [19003] (and in dataset as such) and Shu an error for Wen(2) [18998] (and in dataset as such). All this is in accord with chronological logic and, with the exception of Feigong (and it is possible that Feigong and Zhigong are the same person), all are identified as members of the same lineage. Fujian TZ, 148.18a. CBD, 4, 2910.</note>
